        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 3:18PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking several thunderstorms
across southern Beaverhead and Madison counties with a strong cell
near Lima. These storms were moving east at 20 mph. Wind gusts to 50
mph and lightning may accompany any of these storms with small hail
possible between Lima and Monida Pass.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Virginia City, Lima, Monida, Dell, Bannack Pass, Lakeview, Cameron,
and Snowline.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
